---

<Layout 
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  structuredDataType="WebPage"
  structuredData={{
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Website Cost Guide 2025",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Beach Bird Studios"
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Beach Bird Studios"
    }
  }}
>
  <Header />
  
  <Hero 
    headline="Website Cost Guide for <span class='text-yellow-400'>2025</span>"
    subheadline="Honest pricing breakdown and what you should really expect to pay for a professional website"
    primaryCTA={{
      text: "Get Your Custom Quote",
      href: "/contact"
    }}
    secondaryCTA={{
      text: "View Our Pricing",
      href: "/services/custom-website-design"
    }}
  />

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Website pricing can be confusing and frustrating. You've probably seen prices ranging from $500 to $50,000+ 
          and wondered what the difference actually is. This guide breaks down real website costs in 2025, 
          what affects pricing, and how to ensure you get good value for your investment.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          We'll explore different price points, what you get at each level, and red flags to avoid. 
          By the end, you'll understand what your website should cost and how to make the smartest investment for your business.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-400 p-6 mb-8">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <i data-lucide="dollar-sign" class="h-5 w-5 text-green-400"></i>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-3">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-700">
                <strong>Key Insight:</strong> The cheapest option is rarely the most cost-effective. 
                Focus on value and long-term ROI rather than just upfront costs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Factors -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What Determines Website Pricing?</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Understanding these factors helps you make informed decisions and get quotes that reflect your actual needs.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={pricingFactors} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Price Range Breakdown -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2025 Website Pricing Breakdown</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Here's what you can realistically expect at different price points.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Budget Range -->
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <div class="text-center mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Budget Range</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-600 my-4">$500 - $2,500</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What You Get:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>• Template-based design</li>
              <li>• Basic customization</li>
              <li>• 3-8 pages maximum</li>
              <li>• Limited revisions</li>
              <li>• DIY content management</li>
              <li>• Minimal ongoing support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Best For:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Very small businesses, personal projects, or temporary solutions with extremely limited budgets.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-red-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-red-800 text-sm font-medium">⚠️ Caution: Often includes hidden costs, limited functionality, and minimal support.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Professional Range -->
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-400 rounded-lg p-8 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-4 left-1/2 transform -translate-x-1/2">
            <span class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Most Popular</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="text-center mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Professional Range</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600 my-4">$3,000 - $8,000</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What You Get:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>• Custom design and branding</li>
              <li>• Mobile-responsive layout</li>
              <li>• 8-15 pages</li>
              <li>• SEO optimization</li>
              <li>• Content management system</li>
              <li>• 3-6 month support included</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Best For:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Most small to medium businesses looking for professional online presence and lead generation.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-blue-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium">✓ Sweet Spot: Best balance of features, quality, and value for most businesses.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Premium Range -->
        <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <div class="text-center mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Premium Range</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-purple-600 my-4">$8,000 - $25,000+</div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What You Get:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <li>• Completely custom development</li>
              <li>• Advanced functionality</li>
              <li>• E-commerce capabilities</li>
              <li>• Database integrations</li>
              <li>• Comprehensive SEO strategy</li>
              <li>• 12+ months of support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Best For:</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Large businesses, e-commerce stores, or companies requiring complex functionality and integrations.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-purple-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium">🚀 Enterprise: Maximum functionality, performance, and long-term support.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Website Types -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-cream-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Pricing by Website Type</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Different types of websites have different complexity levels and pricing structures.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={websiteTypes} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hidden Costs -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Hidden Costs to Consider</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Beyond the initial design cost, these ongoing expenses are essential for a successful website.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={hiddenCosts} />
      
      <div class="mt-12 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Annual Website Maintenance Budget</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
          <div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-600 mb-2">$500 - $1,200</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Basic maintenance, hosting, and security for simple business websites</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-600 mb-2">$1,200 - $3,000</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Professional maintenance with SEO, updates, and content management</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-600 mb-2">$3,000 - $8,000+</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Enterprise maintenance with advanced features, marketing, and priority support</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Red Flags -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Red Flags: What to Avoid</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Protect yourself from these common warning signs that indicate potential problems or scams.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={redFlags} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Value Assessment -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Measuring Website Value & ROI</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Focus on these value factors rather than just upfront costs to make the best investment decision.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={valueFactors} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Budget Strategies -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-cream-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Smart Budget Strategies</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Maximize your website investment with these practical approaches to managing costs.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <FeatureGrid features={budgetStrategies} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROI Calculator Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Website ROI Calculator</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Use these scenarios to estimate potential return on your website investment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Local Service Business</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <p><strong>Website Cost:</strong> $5,000</p>
            <p><strong>Monthly Visitors:</strong> 500</p>
            <p><strong>Conversion Rate:</strong> 3%</p>
            <p><strong>Average Job Value:</strong> $800</p>
            <p><strong>Monthly Revenue:</strong> $12,000</p>
            <p><strong>Annual Revenue:</strong> $144,000</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-green-100 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-green-800">ROI: 2,780% in first year</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">E-commerce Store</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <p><strong>Website Cost:</strong> $12,000</p>
            <p><strong>Monthly Visitors:</strong> 2,000</p>
            <p><strong>Conversion Rate:</strong> 2%</p>
            <p><strong>Average Order:</strong> $75</p>
            <p><strong>Monthly Revenue:</strong> $3,000</p>
            <p><strong>Annual Revenue:</strong> $36,000</p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-100 rounded">
            <p class="font-semibold text-blue-800">ROI: 200% in first year</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="text-center text-gray-700">
          <strong>Remember:</strong> These are conservative estimates. Many businesses see much higher returns 
          with proper SEO, marketing, and conversion optimization.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Questions to Ask -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Questions to Ask Before You Hire</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Use these questions to evaluate potential web designers and avoid costly mistakes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Project Scope & Timeline</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>• What exactly is included in the quoted price?</li>
              <li>• How many revisions are included?</li>
              <li>• What is the realistic timeline for completion?</li>
              <li>• What happens if the project scope changes?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Technical Specifications</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>• Will the website be mobile-responsive?</li>
              <li>• What content management system will be used?</li>
              <li>• Are SEO basics included in the development?</li>
              <li>• How will the website perform on different browsers?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Support & Maintenance</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>• What kind of training will you provide?</li>
              <li>• How long is support included after launch?</li>
              <li>• What are your ongoing maintenance options?</li>
              <li>• Who owns the website and content after completion?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">References & Portfolio</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
              <li>• Can you provide references from recent clients?</li>
              <li>• Do you have examples of similar projects?</li>
              <li>• What results have your websites achieved for clients?</li>
              <li>• How do you measure project success?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <CTASection 
    headline="Ready to Get an Honest Quote?"
    description="Let's discuss your project and provide transparent pricing with no hidden costs or surprises."
    primaryCTA={{
      text: "Get Your Custom Quote",
      href: "/contact"
    }}
    secondaryCTA={{
      text: "See Our Portfolio",
      href: "/about"
    }}
  />

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .bg-cream-50 {
    background-color: rgba(245, 230, 211, 0.3);
  }
</style>